<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="crash-v">crash <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /kræʃ/    美 /kræʃ/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-vi-vt">1.★ <strong>vi &amp; vt (使) 发出撞击声；(使) 发出爆裂声：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The plates crashed to the floor.
盘子哗啦一声摔碎在地上。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She stormed out of the room and crashed the door shut behind her.
她愤怒地冲出房间，砰的一声把门关上了。</p></div>

<p>注: crash最初是一个象声词，模仿断裂的声音， “哗啦…”。  </p>
<h4 id="2-vi-vt">2.★ <strong>vi &amp; vt (使飞机) 坠毁；(使汽车等) 猛撞：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The news that the plane had crashed made us sad.
飞机失事的消息让我们非常难过。</p><footer>译林③ – 1</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He <strong>crashed</strong> his car <strong>into</strong> a wall.
他开车撞到了墙上。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He <strong>crashed into</strong> the other youth and they both landed on the ground.
他撞上了另一个年轻人，两个人都摔在地上。</p><footer>2008 上海春</footer></div>

<h4 id="3-vi">3.★ <strong>vi (公司等) 倒闭；(股票) 暴跌；(计算机等) 死机；崩溃：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The company crashed with debts of £2 million.
那家公司倒闭了，留下两百万英镑的债务。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The computers that we use at the moment are old and slow, and they often crash.
我们现在使用的计算机又旧又慢，还经常死机。</p></div></div>